ipts/load-test-engine.ts`)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":321,"content":"pnpm tsx scripts/load-test-engine.ts --workspaces=3 --enrollments=100 --workers=2 --duration=120","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":352,"content":"  - `scripts/load-test-engine.ts` (new)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./scripts/load-test-engine.ts","matches":[{"lineNumber":6,"content":" *   pnpm tsx scripts/load-test-engine.ts --workspaces=3 --enrollments=100 --workers=2 --duration=120","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":7,"content":" *   pnpm tsx scripts/load-test-engine.ts --test-mode=permanent-failure","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":8,"content":" *   pnpm tsx scripts/load-test-engine.ts --test-mode=outer-rollback","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":9,"content":" *   pnpm tsx scripts/load-test-engine.ts --test-mode=suppression-during-run","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":10,"content":" *   pnpm tsx scripts/load-test-engine.ts --test-mode=seg-routing","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./review/findings/testing.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":19,"content":"| **Covered by load test** (not CI) | `scripts/load-test-engine.ts`            |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":23,"content":"**`scripts/load-test-engine.ts`** spawns `--workers=2` with `QUIKSEND_ENGINE_FAKE_MAIL=1` (lines 250-274, 261), seeds active enrollments with pre-captured anchors and `auto_email` steps (lines 140-228), then asserts no duplicate `message.idempotency_key` rows (lines 318-331), no cap breaches, no stuck enrollments, and no dead jobs (lines 333-366). This is the right invariant set for Phase 6 send safety.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":40,"content":"Load test only checks DB uniqueness post-hoc (`scripts/load-test-engine.ts:318-331`), not the skip-send code path.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":271,"content":"| `scripts/load-test-engine.ts`                                                                        | **No** — manual via `tsx` (see file header line 6) | 2 (default) | Full engine: `auto_email` steps, fake mail, concurrent worker processes | Duplicate `idempotency_key`, cap breaches via `send_reservation`, stuck enrollments, dead `job_log` rows (`318-366`) |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":274,"content":"**Difference:** `load-test-engine` is the Phase 6 send-safety proof (fake mail + real sends + richer invariants). `load-test-scheduler` is a lighter scheduler smoke test whose send invariants are largely inert because no messages are produced.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":284,"content":"| Randomized orgs/emails | `withTestOrgs` uses `randomUUID()` for org/user ids and emails (`packages/db/src/testing.ts:69-82`). Load tests use `@loadtest.local` / `@loadtest.quiksend.local` with UUID suffixes (`scripts/load-test-engine.ts:61-62, 186`).                                                                                                                           |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":316,"content":"- What: CI runs `pnpm test` only. `scripts/load-test-engine.ts` and `load-test-scheduler.ts` are manual.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":318,"content":"- Fix: Add a CI job (or nightly) that runs `load-test-engine.ts` with reduced `--enrollments` / `--duration` against the CI Postgres service.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":371,"content":"- Impact: False confidence if only `pnpm load-test` is run, not `load-test-engine.ts`.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":372,"content":"- Fix: Document that `load-test-engine.ts` is the authoritative send-safety script; or align scheduler script to use `auto_email` + fake mail like the engine script.","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":462,"content":"| Scheduler / no double-send (2 workers) | Load test only (`load-test-engine`) | Covered by load test, not CI   |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./review/findings/completeness.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":23,"content":"| **6** Engine                | E1-E4, D core       | **Mostly complete** | Reservations, SKIP LOCKED, advisory lock, idempotency, `job_log` dead path; **`scripts/load-test-engine.ts` has fuller asserts than `pnpm load-test` entrypoint**. |","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":107,"content":"- Location: `packages/db/src/load-test-scheduler.ts:149-179` vs `scripts/load-test-engine.ts:318-364`","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./phase11-review/briefs/completeness.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":79,"content":"- My session note: canary load-test modes were declared but seedCanaryFixture removed. Verify the two `--test-mode=canary-*` modes DON'T claim to work in docs (if docs promise it, that's a completeness gap)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./phase11-review/briefs/architecture.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":76,"content":"    - Any dead code introduced by Wave 7 (functions defined but never called — my session already caught `seedCanaryFixture` in load-test-engine.ts; anything else?)","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./docs/implementations/phases/Quiksend-Implementation-Plan-Phase-11.md","matches":[{"lineNumber":605,"content":"  `scripts/load-test-engine.ts` — seeds 500 prospects across 50 fake domains,","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false},{"lineNumber":1562,"content":"- **Load test extensions** each add a new mode to `scripts/load-test-engine.ts`:","contentTruncated":false,"isContextLine":false}]},{"file":"./.github/workflows/ci.yml","matches":[{"lineNumber":61,"content":"      