{"type":"assistant","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Phase 11 architecture review is done. Findings are in `phase11-review/findings/architecture.md`.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Overall: needs-fixes** (0 critical, 0 high, 1 medium, 5 low)\n\n### Prior-phase invariants — no regressions\n- **CR-009**: `packages/mail` has no `@quiksend/integrations` dependency; `createAdapterForMailbox` injects `NangoProxyClient`\n- **`packages/core` purity**: deliverability modules and entry-conditions are I/O-free\n- **Tenancy**: Phase 11 server functions use `orgFn`; admin gates on write paths\n- **State machine**: `no_safe_mailbox` added cleanly; Wave 6 `applyWebEffects` used for pause/resume/stop and manual anchor\n\n### Main finding (medium)\n**[ARCH-001]** `send_canary` and `emit_canary_bundle` are in the `Effect` union and worker/web executors but are never emitted by `transition()`. Canaries go through enrollment-time `enqueue(\"canary.send\")` instead, which diverges from the spec and leaves dead executor paths.\n\n### Low-severity items\n- SEG gateway lists duplicated in 4 places (drift risk)\n- Dead exports: `newCanaryToken`, `sanitizeForSegAsync`\n- `getSequenceDeliverability` server fn has no UI consumer (PHI live indicator not wired)\n- `gatewayClassification` missing Drizzle `relations()`\n- Worker duplicates `extractDomain` instead of importing from mail\n\n### What’s working well\nMail/integrations decoupling, core purity, tenancy chokepoint, Wave 5/6 effect-executor fixes, shared `isMailboxSafeForGateway`, clean schema/migrations, intentional UI route split, and Foundation stubs fully replaced by TAU’s real gateway detection."}]},"session_id":"aecb96b3-97ce-42b8-80b5-d84ca54271f5"}
